<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFF8FFD9A5F8FB231C33FA64" blockId="8.[136,1452,518,1480]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A5F8FB231F19FAD4" bold="true" box="[189,294,1274,1300]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF8FFD9A463FB231FF1FAD4" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" box="[294,462,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virgata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A463FB231FF1FAD4" box="[294,462,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Aloysia virgata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by larger leaf blades (5‒13 × 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF8FFD9A6FFFB231A09FAD5" box="[954,1078,1274,1301]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.15" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="cm" value="3.15" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="1.7">1.7‒4.6 cm</quantity>
) in comparison with 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF8FFD9A05CFB221B94FAD4" authorityName="Troncoso" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="Gillies &amp; Hooker ex Hooker" box="[1305,1451,1275,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gratissima">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A05CFB221B94FAD4" box="[1305,1451,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. gratissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(0.8‒2.2 × 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFF8FFD9A442FAC71FB4FAF9" box="[263,395,1310,1337]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="cm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3‒0.5 cm</quantity>
), serrate margin (
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A710FAC61C4BFAF8" box="[597,628,1311,1336]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">vs.</emphasis>
entire), main and secondary veins of the adaxial surface prominent (
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A0C8FAC61B9BFAF8" box="[1421,1444,1311,1336]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">vs</emphasis>
. only main vein prominent), and numerous racemes per axil (
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A616FA9A1D55FA9C" box="[851,874,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">vs</emphasis>
. one raceme per axil). The flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFF8FFD9A07DFA9A1B94FA9C" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" box="[1336,1451,1347,1373]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Aloysia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virgata">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFF8FFD9A07DFA9A1B94FA9C" box="[1336,1451,1347,1373]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. virgata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are melliferous and strongly aromatic, being commonly cultivated near apiaries attracting several species of bees (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFF8FFD9A5CAFA531FC0FA64" author="Salimena-Pires, F. R. G. &amp; Giulietti, A. M." box="[143,511,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="155 - 186" refId="ref38083" refString="Salimena-Pires, F. R. G. &amp; Giulietti, A. M. (1998) Flora da Serra do Cipo, Minas Gerais: Verbenaceae. Boletim de Botanica da Universidade de Sao Paulo 17: 155 - 186. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2316 - 9052. v 17 i 0 p 155 - 186" type="journal article" year="1998">Salimena-Pires &amp; Giulietti 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
